#### Academic Offices

Chan’s career has been distinguished by a series of high-profile academic leadership positions, demonstrating a consistent progression through the ranks of university administration.

*   **3rd President of the [Hong Kong University of Science and Technology](/Hong_Kong_University_of_Science_and_Technology):** Serving from September 2009 to August 2018, this was a pivotal period for HKUST. His tenure would have involved guiding the university's strategic development, fostering research excellence, and enhancing its global standing. He succeeded [Paul Chu](/Chu_Ching-wu) and was succeeded by [Wei Shyy](/Wei_Shyy).
*   **3rd President of the [King Abdullah University of Science and Technology](/King_Abdullah_University_of_Science_and_Technology):** From September 2018 to August 2024, he led KAUST. This role placed him at the forefront of a relatively new, research-intensive university with a significant mandate to drive scientific innovation in Saudi Arabia. He followed [Jean-Lou Chameau](/Jean-Lou_Chameau) and was succeeded by [Ed Byrne](/Ed_Byrne_(neuroscientist)).

These presidencies are more than just titles; they represent immense responsibility for shaping the academic future, fostering intellectual communities, and driving research agendas on a global scale.

